President Biden met with Chancellor Scholz of Germany ahead of the G7 Leaders' Summit. They discussed coordinating responses to Russia's invasion of Ukraine, climate change, and economic and democratic resilience. Both leaders expressed their commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and providing support to defend its democracy against Russian aggression. They also talked about mitigating the impacts of Russia's war on global food and energy security. President Biden welcomed Germany's commitment to increase defense spending and meet NATO commitments. They also discussed challenges posed by China and their shared commitment to address global infrastructure gaps.